# Git & GitHub Identity

The GitHub account for this project is **jimni6**.

## Before any push

1. Run `git remote -v` and verify the URL contains `jimni6`
2. Expected formats:
   - `git@github.com:jimni6/<repo>.git`
   - `https://github.com/jimni6/<repo>.git`
3. If the remote points to a different account, stop and ask the user

## Constraints

- NEVER modify `git config --global`
- NEVER push to a remote that does not belong to `jimni6`
- When creating a new remote, always use: `git remote add origin git@github.com:jimni6/<repo>.git`
